    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7, then boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Chop your <strong>leek[s]</strong> in half lengthways, wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top, tail and chop into large chunks</p><p>Crush your <strong>garlic </strong>open by squashing it with the side of a knife and discard the skins</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-cheese-cauliflower-soup-with-cheese-crisps/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pot (with a matching lid!) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped leek</strong> and <strong>onion</strong> to the pan and cook for 4-5 min or until the leek has softened</p><p>Meanwhile, peel your <strong>potato[es]</strong> and chop into bite-sized pieces, then cut your <strong>cauliflower[s]</strong> into small florets</p><p>Slice <strong>half </strong>your <strong>green chilli[es] </strong>into 3 rounds per person, then deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) the <strong>remaining chilli </strong>and roughly chop</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-cheese-cauliflower-soup-with-cheese-crisps/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the leek has softened, add the <strong>crushed garlic </strong>and <strong>chopped potato </strong>with<strong> </strong>1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix and cook for 1-2 min</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-cheese-cauliflower-soup-with-cheese-crisps/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped cauliflower </strong>and<strong> chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) with 600ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[800ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [1L] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>and 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span><strong> milk</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook, with the lid on, for 15 min or until the veg is softened \u2013 this is your<strong> soup base</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-cheese-cauliflower-soup-with-cheese-crisps/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, line a baking tray with <strong>baking paper</strong>, then sprinkle a very thin layer of your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> onto the baking tray into rounds (3 per person!), reserving the <strong>remaining cheese </strong>for later</p><p>Top each round with a slice of <strong>chilli</strong>, then put the tray in the oven for 4-5 min or until the cheese is melted and golden \u2013 these are your <strong>cheese crisps</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-cheese-cauliflower-soup-with-cheese-crisps/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add a small knob of <strong>butter </strong>with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>to a small heatproof bowl and put the bowl in the <strong>microwave </strong>and cook for 20-30 secs or until the butter is melted</p><p>Once the butter is melted, add your <strong>dried chilli flakes </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) and give a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>chilli butter</strong></p><p>Grate your<strong> cheddar cheese </strong>finely</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-cheese-cauliflower-soup-with-cheese-crisps/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the soup base is ready, remove the pot from the heat add your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> and your <strong>umami seasoning </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>pepper</strong>, then blitz with a <strong>(stick) blender</strong> until smooth</p><p>Once smooth, stir through the <strong>grated cheddar</strong> and <strong>remaining grated Italian cheese</strong> and season to taste, then set aside for 4-5 min for the flavours to develop \u2013 this is your <strong>chilli cheese cauliflower soup</strong>, then put your <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong> in the oven for 4 min or until they're hot and crusty</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chilli-cheese-cauliflower-soup-with-cheese-crisps/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>chilli cheese cauliflower soup </strong>and top with the <strong>cheese crisps </strong>and drizzle over the <strong>chilli butter</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>crusty ciabatta </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
